# Niagara System: Dynamic Weather Effects
# Enhances atmospheric tension and affects gameplay mechanics

## EMITTER 1: Rain System
- Spawn Rate: 1000-5000 particles/second (intensity-based)
- Lifetime: 2-4 seconds
- Size: 0.1-0.2 world units (length: 1-3 units)
- Velocity: Downward (10-25 m/s) with wind influence
- Color: Blue-gray (180,200,220,200)
- Material: M_Raindrops_Translucent

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Sky sphere spawn volume
- Velocity: Gravity + wind vector
- Collision: Ground splash effects
- Player Interaction: Visibility reduction
- Fire Interaction: Extinguishes campfires

### Intensity Levels:
- Light_Rain: 1000 particles/sec, minimal gameplay impact
- Medium_Rain: 2500 particles/sec, reduced visibility
- Heavy_Rain: 5000 particles/sec, significant survival challenge

## EMITTER 2: Ground Splash Effects
- Spawn Rate: Triggered by rain collision
- Lifetime: 0.3-0.8 seconds
- Size: 0.2-0.6 world units
- Velocity: Radial burst from impact
- Color: Surface-dependent (mud brown, rock gray)
- Material: M_WaterSplash_Translucent

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Rain collision points
- Surface Detection: Different effects per material type
- Puddle Formation: Accumulation over time
- Player Movement: Footstep splash enhancement

## EMITTER 3: Fog Bank System
- Spawn Rate: 50-200 particles/second
- Lifetime: 20-60 seconds
- Size: 5.0-15.0 world units
- Velocity: Slow horizontal drift (0.5-2.0 m/s)
- Color: Gray-white (200,200,200,100)
- Material: M_Fog_Volumetric

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Ground level spawn areas
- Density Variation: Procedural thickness changes
- Temperature Response: Morning/evening enhancement
- Visibility Impact: Reduces dinosaur detection range

### Gameplay Integration:
- Stealth_Bonus: Player harder to detect in fog
- Predator_Ambush: Dinosaurs can use fog for surprise attacks
- Navigation_Challenge: Landmarks obscured

## EMITTER 4: Wind Particle Indicators
- Spawn Rate: 30-80 particles/second
- Lifetime: 5-10 seconds
- Size: 0.1-0.4 world units
- Velocity: Wind direction vector
- Color: Nearly transparent (255,255,255,50)
- Material: M_WindTrails_Additive

### Behavior Modules:
- Initial Location: Distributed air volume
- Wind Strength Visualization: Speed affects particle behavior
- Directional Indicators: Shows wind patterns
- Environmental Response: Affects other VFX systems

## EMITTER 5: Lightning Flash Effects
- Spawn Rate: Event-triggered (storm conditions)
- Lifetime: 0.1-0.3 seconds
- Size: Screen-wide flash overlay
- Velocity: Instantaneous
- Color: Bright blue-white (255,255,255)
- Material: M_Lightning_Additive

### Behavior Modules:
- Screen Flash: Full-screen brightness spike
- Thunder Delay: Audio follows visual by distance
- Dinosaur Reaction: AI responds to lightning events
- Fire Ignition: Rare chance to start forest fires

### Storm Progression:
- Building_Clouds: Gradual darkening
- Wind_Increase: Escalating particle movement
- Rain_Onset: Precipitation begins
- Lightning_Phase: Electrical activity
- Storm_Peak: Maximum intensity
- Clearing_Phase: Gradual reduction

## SYSTEM PARAMETERS:
- Weather_Intensity: 0.0-1.0 (master control)
- Wind_Direction: Vector3 (affects all wind-influenced effects)
- Temperature: -10.0 to 40.0 (affects fog and steam visibility)
- Humidity: 0.0-1.0 (influences rain probability)
- Storm_Probability: 0.0-1.0 (chance of severe weather)
- Season_Modifier: Affects weather patterns and intensity